# ════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FILE: Appfile
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# WHAT THIS DOES (plain language):
#   Tells fastlane which app this is and which Apple Developer team to use
#   when it talks to App Store Connect. It reads those values from
#   environment variables instead of hardcoding them, because the real
#   values don't exist yet (see the Fastfile header for the full story).
#
# NOTES / GOTCHAS:
#   - Signing credentials do not exist yet — this scaffold is inert until
#     the owner completes Apple Developer Program enrollment and CI
#     secrets (APPLE_TEAM_ID, APPLE_ID, an App Store Connect API key or a
#     signing certificate/profile) are added. Running any lane before then
#     will fail fast with a missing-env-var error, which is the intended,
#     safe failure mode.
#   - app_identifier matches PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER in
#     ios/App/App.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj — keep them in sync if the
#     bundle ID ever changes.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════

app_identifier("com.utahprosrestoration.upr")
apple_id(ENV["APPLE_ID"]) # App Store Connect account email — CI secret, not yet set
team_id(ENV["APPLE_TEAM_ID"]) # Apple Developer Program team ID — CI secret, not yet set

# Only needed if/when an App Store Connect API key (JSON) is used instead of
# apple_id + 2FA for CI auth — left commented until that decision is made.
# itc_team_id(ENV["APPLE_ITC_TEAM_ID"])
